{"id": "firmware-development--zero-hop-data-transfer", "title": "Zero-hop data transfer?", "forum": "firmware-development", "messages": [{"id": "1453153596479766611", "author": "H3JA", "author_handle": "hejali", "user_id": "540167556443406338", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/540167556443406338/f2de57fe58dad5b846bf84187c43b502.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Tuesday, December 23, 2025 5:33 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-23 5:33 p.m.", "text": "Would be nice having some zero hop node-to-node data transfer capabilities. There could be a seperate frequency/preset for it to not overload the main mesh. Atleast maybe some voice messaging or even text files over the traditional limit!", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Would be nice having some zero hop node-to-node data transfer capabilities. There could be a seperate frequency/preset for it to not overload the main mesh. Atleast maybe some voice messaging or even text files over the traditional limit!</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1453158926978777088", "author": "🦦 Hilton Travis SMBI", "author_handle": "hiltontravissmbi", "user_id": "1430489846090043482", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1430489846090043482/d40eb19b82a2cb5fc68c6c0bc7093cc7.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Tuesday, December 23, 2025 5:54 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-23 5:54 p.m.", "text": "That's more a Reticulum thing...", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>That&#39;s more a Reticulum thing...</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1453165310260543616", "author": "H3JA", "author_handle": "hejali", "user_id": "540167556443406338", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/540167556443406338/f2de